tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All laboratory values are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (6.2%), indicating impaired glucose tolerance or possible early diabetes. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are normal. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of lifestyle modification or further evaluation for glycemic control.
